did.unittitle: American Association of School Administrators Collection (AASA) records
did.physloc: Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Gift of the American Association of School Administrators, 2016.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into 8 series: Awards, Constituent relations and communications, Governance and planning, Historic, Publications, AV content and photographs, Membership, Operations and conferences, and Public policy

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way: Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository. Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Series is arranged alphanumerically by title, then chronologically within the same title.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series consists of awards given by or to the American Association of School Administrators, and records about those awards, including event programs and invitations, nominees and award criteria, applications, photographs and slides, and other paperwork. Box 4 contains a commerative plate, and box 9 contains medals.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series primarily contains materials published by the AASA to communicate with members. This includes magazines-especially the School Administrator as it evolved into a modern, glossy publication-as well as audio and video material. In particular, the videos contain interviews and messages from former AASA director Dr. Paul Houston.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists primarily of documents related to the running of AASA, from the daily operations to official platforms and policy positions. Documents includes executive director's travel forms, official endorsements, directories, minutes and documents from meetings, annual reports, and financial documents.

The audio recordings include individual conference sessions, primarily talks. These talks are not individually titled, but rather grouped by the conference they were part of.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Series is arranged alphabetically by title, then chronologically for shared titles.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of material created or held by AASA to explain or promote their agenda in regards to public policy, as well as material from the AASA Committee on Federal Policy and Legislation. The documents are concerned primarily with education policy at the federal level, but one folder contains documents related to healthcare policy. The series includes numerous briefs of amicus curiae written by AASA.
